storyInfo: On a field mission, Blemishine meets two brothers, and in these brothers, she seems to see some hint of herself and her sister.

attributes.content: A group of bandits who fled here... So Rhodes Island takes jobs like this too?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Yep. Given our branch offices operate under all sorts of conditions all across the world, any weird and wild commission could come to our doors.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: But it IS usually just responding to some Infected or Originium.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: According to the info the office gave, the village militia'll help us with the operation. Says their chief's a pretty impressive one.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: We already spent a chunk of time just getting here. I hope nothing happened in the meanwhile...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: You're Rhodes Island, here to help us catch the bandits?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Yes, we are.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: You're the head of the village militia. Was Lanton the name?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: No, I'm his brother Landi. The thing with him, well...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Not long ago, while he was leading a team on patrol, they got attacked. The others were alright, but he went missing. We've searched for ages without turning up any trace of him, so now it's up to me to lead the militia until we get him back.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I'm sorry. If we'd only come a bit sooner...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: It's not your fault. It takes time for Messengers to pass the word on, after all.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I'm just hoping you can help out with catching those bandits. It'll take a weight off the village's shoulders.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Our intel says a group of bandits stole a merchant caravan's Originium weapons, and then fled this way.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: That tells us these bandits are no pushovers.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Right now, it's highly likely they're eyeing the village, so all of you stay here to protect against potential raids.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But––
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: They're going, so it's up to us. No harm in that.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Gerain, those bandits are the reason my brother's missing now!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: And? Lanton's the strongest in the village. If they can send him missing, what good'll we do if we go?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: And what good'll you do, Landi?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: I don't want an argument with you.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Only catching these bandits can bring peace to the village.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: How? With your 'superior' command skills? No idea how we usually patrol, no idea how we even form our squads, is that all it takes?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Or your 'genius' leadership where you can't even remember all our names?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: You can't seriously think you're Lanton, can you?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Come again?!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: That's my point for today.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Do you think we see you as a decent stand-in for the captain? You're just a shame on Lanton, that's it.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: You've never drilled with us, all you do is hunt in the mountains all day. The idea of protecting the village's never even occurred to you.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Lanton's gone, and you suddenly pipe up saying you'll be our militia chief in place of him? What good is you protecting the village going to do? What's going on in your head?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Look, you even made a point of carrying Lanton's sword. Who are you fooling?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Back me up here!
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: He's right! I got fed up a long time ago.
attributes.name: Militiaman B

attributes.content: Damn straight. What gives you the right to boss us around, Landi?
attributes.name: Militiaman C

attributes.content: Alright, let's go, forget him!
attributes.name: Militiaman B

attributes.content: There it is. Enough, Landi. Leave it to these outsiders.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: They'll get a lot more done than you, that much's plain to see.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Your dream is taken from another. Your conviction is borrowed.
attributes.name: Nightmare Knight

attributes.content: You use your young age as an excuse for your confusion... but what point is there?
attributes.name: Nightmare Knight

attributes.content: The world can laugh at the Radiant Knight's stubbornness, but no one may refute the strength in her actions.
attributes.name: Nightmare Knight

attributes.content: Yet you... you are not even a knight.
attributes.name: Nightmare Knight

attributes.content: Well...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: No bearing on me if they don't go. I'll be following you.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: You'll need someone to show the way, right?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Let him come with, Blemishine.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: Alright...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I haven't seen anyone fishy around this area, or any signs people stopped over.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Not bad, dude. Didn't think you could actually walk it on top of talking it.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: If you can't think about what to say, I suggest you keep your mouth shut.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: It's alright. Hunting really is the only thing I'm good for.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Let's go and check ahead.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Also... I'm sorry. For that whole scene you had to see.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: It's not that they're unwilling to help you, they're just not willing to help me.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Why are they so opposed to you?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Because... I guess because I've taken up my brother's post.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: My grandpa was the last militia chief. He trained Lanton and me when we were little.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: We're right on the border here. Bandits on the run, bounty hunters, you name it, they show up in droves. Once we were grown, Grandpa wanted us to protect the village from harm, together.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But—I'm not even good at people like my brother is. I'm better off alone.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: It's like they said, I've never drilled with them. I just like hunting in the mountains on my own.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton understood how I felt, so he became militia leader.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: That was never a problem, up until he went missing.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: (Exhale)...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: The sword you're using now—that's your brother's?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: It's his saber. Apparently, it was found close to where he went missing.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I picked it up because I wanted to use it on those bandits who hurt him.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: This sword's too heavy for you. It's not a good fit for you at all.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: That's alright. I'll use it to make the bandits pay.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But––
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Watch out!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Hnph!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Who are you?!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Dammit.
attributes.name: Bandit

attributes.content: Hold it!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Wait, don't just run off!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Ugh, take them down first!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Stay where you are!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton, it's you, isn't it?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: ...Landi.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton, your clothes. The bandits who attacked us were wearing these.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: You've always been smart. You should be able to guess.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: This means you're working with those bandits...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Right.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I don't want to be trapped in a remote hellhole like that all my life, Landi.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I don't want to spend my whole life bossing around some idiots forever.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: That's all there is to it.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Guh...
attributes.name: Bandit

attributes.content: That's a decent number of targets...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Blemishine, leave this to us. You go find Landi.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: You probably have a bad feeling about this, just like I do.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: Right.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Then go. Don't wait around to confirm that feeling.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: Relax. We can handle this thing.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: Sure can.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: Got it!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Landi, why are you holding my sword?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Didn't you always think my sword was too heavy? Always saying your dagger fit you better?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You obviously know why.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: You weren't like this before.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Oh, I wasn't?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: This is how I should be, then.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I always had to protect the village, to be a role model. I never truly let myself loose.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I never experienced what it's like to mouth off at people.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: And now I know! It feels amazing!
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Gngh...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I hear them talking. They're right in front...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Landi—
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: And you, Landi.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You know, I've always wanted to be like you, no one's lives on my back, just me looking after myself, going into the mountains to hunt, day in, day out, right?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: And now, I know how you feel.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: It's great, absolutely great! No wonder you never got sick of it!
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton, was it my fault you had to take up all that responsibility?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Maria, tell me the truth.
attributes.name: Margaret

attributes.content: Did I rob you of your dreams?
attributes.name: Margaret

attributes.content: Maybe.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: All I can tell you is I plan to experience a hell of a lot I never experienced before. Steal a thing or two, burn a building or three.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Maybe even... kill a couple people.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton raises the knife in his hands, brandishing it at Landi without an ounce of hesitation.
As if it wasn't his younger brother before him, but a simple logjam blocking his way.
Stop!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Hmph... your backup's here, huh.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You'd kill your own brother?!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Why not? I chose this path. He might be my brother, but right now he's in my way.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Landi, get up!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: You're supposed to protect the village!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Lanton...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I know this is partially my fault, that you turned into this. I'm so sorry.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But if you're going to destroy the village over it... then I'll stop you.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I'm going to protect our village!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Protect it?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: What are you talking about, Landi?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: When have you ever protected the village?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: What have you done for the village that gives you the right to talk yourself up like this?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Do Gerain and the rest put any faith in you? Do you know how to assign them? Do you know what a militiaman should do? You know jack squat.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: And even then, you've got the nerve to come up to me and say you're going to protect the village?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I'll learn how!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: When? Now? Not going to happen, little brother.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Don't force your selfishness onto others!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Stop her!
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Ungh.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Landi, you ought to carry on with your little life.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: And after I destroy the village, you ought to run.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You, standing here now, all righteous while you tell me things I used to say, pretending the dream I had is now yours...
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You look absolutely ridiculous.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Why?! Am I wrong for wanting to protect the village?!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: You're not wrong, you're just—
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: A little late to it.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: With a 'clang,' the sword in Landi's hand breaks in two.
Guh... ahh...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: No more dreaming, Landi.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Leave the village. Find somewhere new to live.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Landi...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Blemishine, am I really the one in the wrong?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Was it my fault for not sharing some of my brother's responsibility a bit sooner?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: For being so selfish, just looking after myself?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: How should I answer him?
Should I tell him he's wrong? But is he really wrong?
Should I tell him he's right? But does he really believe it?
Blemishine! Are you guys alright?
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: We're fine... what about over there?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I caught two suckers, and shook the position of the bandit stronghold from them. We can head there now to sweep them up, no problem.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: There are more of them than we estimated. With just the few of us, we probably have no way of clearing them out in one go.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: We need to head back and mobilize that village militia.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: Alright. Let's go, then.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: In a confined room, the sound of metal on metal rings with no respite.
With a serious look, Blemishine beats away at a metal chunk reddening, as if what she hammers into shape is her own will.
Margaret, what he asked his older brother, it's—surprising, actually, how similar it is to what you asked me.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: 'Did I rob you of your dreams?'
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But it's the other way round here, funnily enough.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Honestly, I feel like it's a mutual question.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I could say, in the past, it was me being obsessed with smithing that made you even more enthusiastic about the knight competitions.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: And when I say that, it's me blaming myself for losing you your right to choose.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I could also say it was your enthusiasm for knight competitions that led me to get so much more obsessed with smithing.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But when I say that, it seems like I'm blaming you for losing me my dreams.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: It's like it makes sense either way, and makes no sense either way.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I kind of understand now. People only put it in terms like these when they're trying to settle accounts.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: In times like these, everyone's just trying to push the guilt onto the other side. They don't actually consider things to be that way.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: In reality, how do you even say things like this straight?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: We grew up together, we impacted each other. That's how we came to understand each other.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Blemishine, are you forging a weapon?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: No, it's a sort of way to concentrate that I learned from a colleague named Vulcan.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: It's not to forge weapons, it's to purge my own distracting thoughts.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Do you want to try it too? It's really effective.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Ha ha, not this time.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I came to pass on word. Most of the militia are willing to join the bandit clear operation. The village is readying supplies and weapons right now.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: What about you?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: To be honest, you're a lot like me.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I have an older sister, myself.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: My sister's like your brother. She always shouldered a responsibility that, maybe, me and her should've taken on together.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: And I took her protection for granted, doing what I wanted to do.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: As a side note, what I like doing is smithing of all kinds, making all sorts of weapons and equipment. The armor I'm wearing now, I made myself.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: This hunk of metal's not bad. Let's go with it.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: It was all until one day, because of—certain reasons, my sister was forced to leave home, and go far, far away.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: It was only after that, I realized, how much she was shielding me.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I'm like you, too, trying to take on the responsibility she once took on for me.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Then... did you succeed?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I failed, eheh.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: When I tried to take that responsibility, I got so much criticism, but out of it all, I think what most cut to the core was—
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Someone said my dreams were borrowed.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I've never seen the sights my sister saw, and I've never walked the path she went.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: When things seemed like they were about to come crumbling down, it was only then I suddenly realized, oh—it seems like I should do something, and then I went to do it, and practically, I failed.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Hmm... this furnace is just too old! Once I'm done using it, I think I'll give it a revamp.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: My sister might say I did well, but I know in actuality, it was far from enough.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: The one way I'm luckier is... my sister came back in the end, and once again, she took up the responsibility she held before.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: And she does even more now, and even better.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: While my brother couldn't stand the burden, and chose to abandon his duty.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I already failed.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Why even tell me all this?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I've never regretted my obsession with smithing, and I don't feel my decision to pick up my sister's burden midway was wrong.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I'm hoping I can pass those ideas onto you.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I know I wasn't properly prepared, and I know I wasn't enough to walk the path she walked, in her shoes.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But even if I've experienced, and confirmed that for myself, I still feel proud of taking that step.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Maybe I couldn't get far down the way of the knight, but at least I know I didn't stray from my own beliefs.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: You're so strong.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Not at all. I'd crumple in training and beg Auntie Zofia to go easy on me, and I almost started crying when Margaret came back.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: And I had no time to work on my beloved smithing.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But—I don't consider blood ties, or family, or whatever other bonds like that to be an obstacle.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: So, when I've got no option except to take up the responsibility, I don't feel anything wrong with that.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: That's my answer.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I want to know yours.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I always enjoyed all that my brother gave me, took it for granted too.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: When I saw him like that, I felt guilty.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But I'm part of this village, and I still want to protect it.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: It doesn't matter if I was called a slouch. It doesn't matter if I'm not trusted... I don't want these things to bring me regret.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: So... I guess what I mean is it's the least I can do to fight off my brother.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But I don't know what to do...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Hand that broken sword over, here.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I'll forge you a weapon that fits you.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: That sword's too heavy for you. It'll make your center of gravity wildly unstable, and you won't have a good hold over the power.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: You can't deploy your full strength using a weapon that doesn't suit you.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: If my sister was here, she'd head the charge on their camp. She'd topple every last one of them.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But I'm a craftsman, and the way craftsmen help others, is by putting the best tools in their hands, making them stronger still.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Margaret, in some sense, aren't these brothers just us from another timeline?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: One where you renounced the path of knighthood, wandered the four corners of the land.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: And I took on your ideals for real, and I became a true knight.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Wow, just what kind of world would that've been? I can't imagine you having fallen at all, and I can't picture me becoming a real knight either.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But the knight novels have those sorts of knights too, who've fallen from grace while still holding fast to their creeds. That also seems really cool, in a way.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Ugh. Purge my thoughts, purge my thoughts.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I heard the story. Lanton's...
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Gerain, I'm sorry...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: What are you sorry for? He betrayed us, so now, he's the enemy. Simple as that.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Gerain, from today, I'll be joining you for training.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: What's this? You can't still be treating yourself like Lanton now?
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: I'm not treating myself like him. I'm just treating myself as this village's militia chief.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Whatever.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Several days later...
Hah!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Whew, that's some tricksy blade.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: Can you block him?
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: Sure. But those last few moves just now, at the very least they're closing on an investigative operator's standard.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: Blooming like this in just a few short days, we could refer him to join us if we get the chance.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: Ohh, I'm having a little flashback to the time Auntie Zofia was training me...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: How did she throw moves at me, again... ah, right, like this, probably!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Take this!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Ngh...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Plus my own follow-up!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Blemishine, to be honest, I'm already more or less used to the effects of your Arts.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Look at him, he puts on a pretty good show when he fights serious.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Seriously, what's Landi been doing coming to train with us the last few days?
attributes.name: Militiaman B

attributes.content: Hmph. It's what he should've been doing all along.
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Right here!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Shame I already figured you'd gotten used to it. That's why I readied my posture way in advance!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But you've shaped up massively, haven't you!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Let's go again!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Hold on, come with me.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Here. It's the longsword I forged for you.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: It's just like Lanton's...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Yep, I made it according to that form~ Try wielding it a little.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: So light...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: How is it? Feels a lot easier to use, right?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I really don't know how I should thank you...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: It's alright, don't worry! I'm just glad seeing you cheer up!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Now then, let's set out, and get all those bandits dealt with!
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Hmph, you came after all.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You don't seem surprised.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: We need time to prep resources to attack the village, you need time to prep resources to wipe us out. It's a game of speed.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You've won, that's all. Nothing to be surprised at there.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton...
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Leave the others to us. He's yours, Landi.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Right.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Looks like you chose to take on my burden... Here I thought, after breaking that sword, you could find some freedom too.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I won't judge you, Lanton. But—I don't think you can truly gain freedom by running away from your responsibilities.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: That's just because you haven't fled far enough. Haven't gone all the way.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Hm? Your weapon...
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: A noble tailored it for me after reforging your sword. From here on, I'll use it to protect our village.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Oh... good swordsmanship. You've improved some.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Do you know what it means to take on those responsibilities?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You'll become a symbol to all the people, a mouthpiece of so-called protection, a personification of justice, so on. The one thing not included is you yourself.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Your life'll be a hundred times more painful than it used to be.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: And none of this was yours. And it shouldn't be yours either.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Since I was young, I've been determined to become that. And I chose to give up in the end, while you just lifted the ideal from my hands midway. How long can you bear it?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I regret it a lot, Lanton. I should've talked with you sooner, shared in your feelings. And maybe, after we understood each other better, none of this would've turned out the way it has.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: You ask me how long I can bear it. I'm going to try my hardest to avoid using the word 'bear.'
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I'll strive to work hard with the others, and turn endurance into fondness, into enjoyment.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I don't know if I can do it, but I want to try.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: You want to say you'll do better than me.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: There's no reason to compare the two of us.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Drop dead.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I'm sorry.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Got them all tied up. That ought to put a bow on things.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: So? What do you plan to do with me?
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton, are you really not going to change your mind?
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: The moment I decided to do this, I became a different person.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: You can treat me like a stranger and off me. I love you, Landi, and that's the last thing I can do for you as your older brother.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: This whole month, I've done a lot of things I never did before. I've drawn a joy from it I never knew in the past twenty-something years.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: I may not be satisfied, but it's enough.
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: ... (Unties)
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Go, Lanton.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: The farther, the better.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Don't look back, don't come back, don't regret it.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Or else, I'll kill you.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Lanton.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I'm sorry, Lanton.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: If you looked back, I wouldn't have killed you.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But if I really did just let you go like this, so many more people would've died.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: It's how... it should be...
attributes.name: Elder Hunter

attributes.content: He was in the right, Blemishine.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: I know...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I just never imagined, things could—reach this point, between family.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I'm sorry, Rhodes Islanders. I had to do this.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: We understand.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: Give him a proper burial.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: ...I'll help you.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Lanton, this was the place you loved to train with your sword. I'll bury you here.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I don't know if I can become a militia chief as mighty as you were.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But I'll try my hardest.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I'm very thankful to all of you Rhodes Islanders. Without you, I really have no idea how things would've turned out.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: The militia are all waiting for you. You've truly become their new leader. Go say a few words to them.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: Listen up, everyone.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: What my brother's done, I won't try to argue for him.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: The man I was is a far cry from him, you could see that, and I know that much. I was lazy, idle, and didn't do what I should've.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: But—I'm part of the village too.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: It's my wish to see the village improve, to protect it.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: From here on, in place of my brother, I'll take up the responsibility of protecting the village.
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: I hope you will all support me!
attributes.name: Young Hunter

attributes.content: ... (Clapping)
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: I wasn't convinced before, Landi, but I think I've come over today!
attributes.name: Militiaman B

attributes.content: Landi, give it what you've got! I'll watch your back!
attributes.name: Militiaman A

attributes.content: Blemishine, what's up? Relief all over your face.
attributes.name: Guard Operator

attributes.content: I always had some lingering fears.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I always thought me and my sister getting along was as natural as anything, and it would carry on just like that.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But now I know. I've just been lucky enough...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: If at the time, I actually did fluke my way into winning the whole thing, and when Margaret came back, I'd turned into an outstanding competition knight—
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Would I have become her enemy, maybe?
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I have no idea.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Don't go thinking about it.
attributes.name: Caster Operator

attributes.content: I know, I know.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Standing where I am, I've already realized, what I was thinking would probably never happen...
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: Because I'd never, ever end up in that position.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: The old me would say it's because she suits it better than I do.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: But now, I'd like to say it's because—I know that being where I am suits me better.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: I don't need the spotlight shone on me. If she can carry the equipment I've cast for her to stand in that light, that's enough for me.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: If she wants a sword, then I'll forge her the sharpest sword. If she wants a shield, I'll forge her the sturdiest shield.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: If she wants a way, then, well, I'll forge her the best tools to open it.
attributes.name: Blemishine

attributes.content: That's all there is to it.
attributes.name: Blemishine
